    • Method Detail

      • illegalStmtEncountered

        int illegalStmtEncountered(org.apache.jena.graph.Node graphNode,
                           org.apache.jena.graph.Triple triple,
                           long count)
        Receives notification of illegal statement (triple/quad) during loading. This method is called when an illegal statement (triple/quad) is encountered.
        Parameters:
        graphNode - - node of the named graph. This is only relevant when dealing with named graphs.
        triple - - the offending triple
        count - - the number of triples processed so far.
        Returns:
        0 if this illegal statement should be skipped.

      • statusChanged

        void statusChanged(long count)
        Receives notification of a status change. This method is called when the specified number of triples/quads has been reached during a long-running operation.
        Parameters:
        count - the current number of triples/quads processed
